
// The code snippet demonstrates the use of the [add] slot to append nodes to the children of the [data.read] node. It retrieves nodes specified by the expressions in [get-nodes] for [limit], [offset], [order], and [direction] from the [.arguments] node, and adds them to the [data.read] node's children. This is useful for dynamically constructing a data query based on input arguments.
add:x:./*/data.read
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/limit
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/offset
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/order
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/direction
